Lagos – Ladan Bosso, Head Coach of Nigeria’s U-20 Boys (Flying Eagles) has called up 40 players for next month’s WAFU B U20 Championship in Niamey, Niger Republic. The tournament will holds between May 7 and 20, 2022. In Group A are host Niger; Cote d’Ivoire; Togo and Benin Republic while in Group B are Nigeria; Ghana and Burkina Faso. The top two teams will represent West African in the U20 African Cup of Nations. The invited players are Orya Joseph; Nathaniel Nwosu; Jimoh Saheed; and Chijioke Anianboso – goalkeepers. Defenders are Njoke Augustine; Gabriel Adewara; Babaji Abubakar; Okoli Augustine; Hassan Shuaibu; Uzochukwu Ezeobi; Opeyemi Omoloye; Frederick Benjamin; Monsuru Oyinmade; Adegbite Emmanuel; Bolu Shotimade; and Adamu Saidu. Midfielders are Anas Hassan; Okeowo Oluwaseyi; Shehu Sada; Promise Harrison; Lawal Samson; Clinshak Longba; Aminu Muhammad; Abdulmajeed Ibrahim; Onuche Ogbelu; Jejeko Ola; Hussaini Garba; Divine Nwachukwu; Sulaiman Kirki; Munir Idris; Aminu Yahaya; Tolulope Simon Ojo; and Muhammad Sambo Shehu. Forwards are Emmanuel Ogbole; Ifeanyi Ogba; Sopurochukwu Kelechi; Henry Ndubuisi; Ibrahim Yahaya; Aliyu Abdullahi and Ahmed Abdullah.